1
00:00:29,640 --> 00:00:30,436
Rinkham,

2
00:00:31,020 --> 00:00:32,356
open the door for me.

3
00:00:38,240 --> 00:00:39,070
Rinkham,

4
00:00:39,450 --> 00:00:40,720
open the door for me.

5
00:00:43,409 --> 00:00:45,400
I woke up late, I am just about to head out.

6
00:00:53,530 --> 00:00:54,307
Is that so?

7
00:00:59,550 --> 00:01:01,661
And how is your bodyguard taking care of you?  Is he doing a good job?

8
00:01:03,770 --> 00:01:04,806
Very well.

9
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:15,753
Good to hear.

10
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:39,735
I am nearly dying

11
00:01:40,270 --> 00:01:41,686
and barely unable to breathe.

12
00:01:44,780 --> 00:01:48,726
So a bodyguard like you can feel fear too?

13
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:51,981
I’m not afraid.

14
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,750
I’m just afraid of dying here.

15
00:01:56,970 --> 00:02:04,178
You know, those who are afraid usually have a guilty conscience.

16
00:02:05,460 --> 00:02:10,344
What did you do wrong last night

17
00:02:12,178 --> 00:02:14,170
to be this terrified of my dad?

18
00:02:18,940 --> 00:02:20,258
Because to me,

19
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:23,630
who you really are

20
00:02:26,310 --> 00:02:29,083
doesn't matter as much as what we feel for each other

21
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:34,240
right now.

22
00:02:54,410 --> 00:02:55,993
I really must go now.

23
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:03,624
I used to think you were good at hiding,

24
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,104
but you are terrible at hiding your feelings.

25
00:03:11,110 --> 00:03:12,553
You are teasing me.

26
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:15,310
And what are you going to do about it?

27
00:03:24,570 --> 00:03:25,876
I really must go.

28
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:28,775
Sigh...

29
00:03:30,670 --> 00:03:34,750
My bodyguard never listens to his master.

30
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:42,572
I only listen when it is appropriate.

31
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:48,455
And what matters are inappropriate?

32
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:54,867
Those that make me forget my duty.

33
00:03:58,030 --> 00:04:04,104
In that case, I shall make you forget even more.

34
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:25,446
A few nights ago, I dropped my ruby sash-chain into this river.

35
00:04:26,730 --> 00:04:29,156
I want you to dive down and find it for me.

36
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:36,880
You...

37
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:40,375
you aren't just looking for an excuse to play a trick on me again, are you?

38
00:04:41,580 --> 00:04:42,701
Who knows?

39
00:04:45,310 --> 00:04:48,461
All I know is that I love it dearly.

40
00:04:49,193 --> 00:04:51,190
If you cannot find it,

41
00:04:52,030 --> 00:04:53,513
I will be utterly heartbroken.

42
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:01,556
Lady,

43
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,498
what are you having Kaew do?

44
00:05:05,170 --> 00:05:07,630
I am having him search for my ruby sash-chain.

45
00:05:08,630 --> 00:05:11,101
But isn't that sash-chain in your room?

46
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:16,572
Are you teasing him again?

47
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:20,824
I only want to see how much he is willing to do for me.

48
00:05:42,820 --> 00:05:43,950
How is Kaew doing?

49
00:05:44,350 --> 00:05:46,627
At first, I could still see him diving and searching.

50
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:48,375
But now, he's nowhere to be seen.

51
00:05:49,858 --> 00:05:51,181
Then where did he go?

52
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,046
I do not know, my lady.

53
00:05:53,089 --> 00:05:55,495
Ever since he went into the water, he hasn't resurfaced.

54
00:06:09,910 --> 00:06:14,381
Kaew, come out this instant!

55
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:20,264
Kaew, do not play around like this!

56
00:06:24,010 --> 00:06:26,972
Kaew, come out this instant!

57
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:32,713
Kaew, do not play around like this!

58
00:06:49,330 --> 00:06:50,812
Where have you been?

59
00:06:50,855 --> 00:06:52,810
I was worried sick about you.

60
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:59,360
I couldn't find it, so I went to take a rest.

61
00:06:59,910 --> 00:07:01,206
How could you possibly find it?

62
00:07:01,243 --> 00:07:02,836
It didn't actually fall.

63
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:10,123
So, this is another one of your pranks?

64
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,760
I only…

65
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,316
It is fine.

66
00:07:17,790 --> 00:07:20,910
Seeing you cry because you were worried about me like this…

67
00:07:22,110 --> 00:07:23,372
I would say it was well worth it.

68
00:07:24,180 --> 00:07:25,673
Who is crying because of you?!

69
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,495
Stop following me.

70
00:07:50,740 --> 00:07:52,584
You really love catching me.

71
00:07:54,461 --> 00:07:56,018
Well, you are careless.

72
00:07:57,740 --> 00:08:01,206
Then, if I can protect myself,

73
00:08:01,710 --> 00:08:03,187
you will no longer help me?

74
00:08:05,070 --> 00:08:06,658
If it could be that way, it would be for the best.

75
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:12,566
Fine. Then teach me.

76
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,141
Teach you what?

77
00:08:25,340 --> 00:08:26,190
Fine.

78
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:28,892
Teach me how to use a sword.

79
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:42,978
Don't you see how weak I am?

80
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:47,655
If one day you are no longer by my side,

81
00:08:48,740 --> 00:08:49,956
what am I to do?

82
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,467
Or are you afraid that I might become better than you?

83
00:09:04,780 --> 00:09:06,553
If you truly wish to learn,

84
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:08,178
I will teach you.

85
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:13,673
Excellent. My bodyguard.
